name: "Robo-Panic" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Paint pen, brush pen, liner pen, and Sharpie on reclaimed cardboard with digital embellishments.] The screech of tires and a shrill electronic scream shatter the calm of the night as Buzby wheels past us in a stone-cold, robo-panic... We don't see what he's escaping from until it's too late... ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
